reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic travel bag!
reviews.reviewText: I purchased it off other reviews. They were correct! It is a fantastic travel bag. They day I received it-my husband had bought himselfa bag at Lululemon. When he opened this one on Christmas, the Lululemon bag got thrown in the back of the closet. Lol. He likes this one SO much better. The quality is top notch. The fabric is high quality, and there is a lot of attention to detail, in the bag design. This is the perfect travel bag for a guy. It’s rugged/manly and classy/stylish at the same time. He even got a compliment on it, when he was putting it up in the overhead bin on the plane. If you need a travel bag, this is the one. Sorry Lulu.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Gave as a Christmas gift to my son. He loves it and has already used it. He liked it even more after using! Feels quality and sturdy. Looks great and all zippers work smoothly. Great size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My spouse took this on a conference. He’s just returned. It was perfect for 3 days. He got a extra pair of shoes in the compartment as well. Durable and rugged. I will probably gift one to our son. Heavy duty zippers, and handles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Seems like a good quality duffel
reviews.reviewText: I was excited to get this bag. Seems like a lot of people like it. I do like the style of the bag and the way it opens into separate compartments. Feels like a bag that will last for some time.I knocked it down a star for the color. I ordered gray, which it is, but it has a purple hue to it. After looking at it for a bit, I knew this would bug me. I’m going to get a different color I think. This isn’t a big deal for some, but it was enough for me to not keep it.Overall, it’s a great weekend or travel bag. The design is well thought out, not too many pockets, nice leather handles and straps. Has a nice weathered look too. Good value. Recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable but a tad heavy
reviews.reviewText: I like it but it's a tad heavy. No biggie though. Holds a lot with extra pockets.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High Quality with Low Price
reviews.reviewText: The bag is the perfect size for a weekend trip and I was surprised at its overall quality for the price. I especially like the four small side pockets on the outside. They are great for sunglasses, readers or pens that you need to be able to access quickly. Nice large front outside pocket with magnetic closures is great for a reader or a tablet. Back zippered outside pocket is where I put my chargers and cables. The large interior pocket can fit a few changes of clothes and a small toiletry bag. There are two interior pockets as well with mesh fabric with are great for underwear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love for short trips
reviews.reviewText: I use this bag for weekend trips. Has plenty of room for all you need. I appreciate the different zipper pockets inside to help separate things and stay organized. The pockets at the end I use for my sun glasses cases. The extra side pockets help store even more small items for easy accessibility. Love the color and adjustable carrying strap.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This bag is awesome. Seems very durable. Looks great. It has dividers on each side which is good for separating dirty vs clean when traveling. I thought it seemed a little small, but quickly realized these types of bags are similar size so they can fit as carry ons. Anyway, highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I haven’t used it much yet but it seems well built especially around the usual fail points (zip and strap clips)What did surprise me was the capacity, when first unpacked I really thought it was too small and nearly returned itI then put a pair of jeans, 4 off shirts/shorts/socks, a wash bag, a pair of boots and a fleece jacket in and there was still plenty of slackIf it lasts as well as it looks and performs then a good purchase
